    "Static analysis techniques are widely employed to construct precise test contexts.",
    "Addressing the common challenges of object instantiation and dependency injection in unit testing, researchers leverage static analysis to extract key class dependencies and method signatures, thereby preventing generation failures caused by information deficiency.",
    "To overcome these obstacles, researchers extensively adopt static analysis to build an information-rich context, which is subsequently injected into the prompt before the LLM begins generation.",
    "This process encompasses several key elements.Dependency Graph Construction.",
    "To address complex dependency issues, frameworks such as ChatUniTest [27] and RUG [28] leverage static analysis to construct comprehensive type dependency graphs or object construction graphs (OCG)."
